        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 23 at 6:13PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 613 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 11 miles northwest of Folsom to 16
miles north of Abbott, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Des Moines, Folsom and Capulin.

This includes Highway 64 between Mile Markers 360 and 402.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.</instruction>
